Russians warned about fake calls from banks
In Russia, the number of calls from scammers who replace the phone number of the bank has increased.
It is reported by "Kommersant" with reference to the data of the Central Bank.
In the summer of 2019, the regulator transferred to telecom operators information about more than 2.5 thousand numbers from which customers of various financial organizations were called.
In 189 cases, operators found a number spoofing.
Another 218 rooms were blocked, and in 59 cases a restriction was imposed on the use of financial services.
Deputy Head of the Information Security Department of the Central Bank Artem Sychev said that a wide range of Russian banks faced with the substitution of the number.
He explained that operators do not always respond to the warnings of the Central Bank about fraudulent calls, referring to the absence of such an obligation in the law "On Communications".
Otkritie Bank, Rosbank and Alfa-Bank confirmed the information about the increase in the number of fraudulent calls with the substitution of the number.
According to the press service of Beeline, some of the information about fraudulent calls, which was transferred by the Central Bank, was incorrect: the lists included numbers that are really used by banks to communicate with customers.
Blocking them would lead to disruptions in the work of the organization.
Artem Sychev said that the Central Bank plans to create a database of fraud numbers, which the telecom operator will contact with each call to check the number.
He explained that in order to create such a base, it would be necessary to amend the legislation.
