Regions were invited to share the secrets of business support
As it became known to the "Parliamentary Gazette", on September 27, the Chairman of the Federation Council Committee on Economic Policy Andrei Kutepov sent a letter to the Minister of Economic Development Maxim Oreshkin and the Minister of Finance Anton Siluanov with a proposal to express a position on the initiatives of the subjects of the Federation to improve legislation in the field of supporting small and medium-sized businesses (SMEs).
It's time to establish interregional ties
The Federation Council Committee on Economic Policy summarized the information received from the regions about the current programs for business development and legalization of the self-employed, as well as about the results of such programs.
In their letters, the regions told the senators about the problems of SME development and sent proposals for improving the current legislation.
"To date, communication between the regions is not sufficiently established, as a result of which the business community in all regions of the visit of senators identified the issue of the lack of information on regional programs for the development of entrepreneurship in the whole country," Andrei Kutepov stated.
In the annex to the letter sent to the Government, he presented a set of positive developments of the regions on the legalization of self-employment and summary data from the regions with proposals and problems (available to the editorial board).
In addition to the relevant ministries, summary data from the regions were also sent to the heads of regional executive bodies.
The exchange of information on positively implemented developments in the regions could give impetus to the development of entrepreneurship as a whole.
The first step towards such an exchange will be to send the information available to the Committee on Economic Policy," the senator told the Parliamentary Gazette.
Useful experience
Today, in many regions of the country, programs to support small and medium-sized businesses have been adopted and are successfully operating.
For example, in the Vologda region there is a Center for Entrepreneurship Support, which, in addition to financial support measures, assists businessmen in certifying finished products.
In the Ivanovo region, a business support system has been developed, providing for the implementation of the principle of one window through multifunctional centers.
In the Krasnodar Territory, start-up agricultural consumer cooperatives are provided with grants from the regional budget.
In the Oryol region, there is a center for cluster development.
The Amur Region within the framework of the federal project "Acceleration of Small and Medium-Sized Businesses" provides for the possibility of subsidizing business incubators created on the basis of existing non-state coworking centers at the expense of the federal budget.
And in a number of other regions, special support measures are being taken for youth entrepreneurship.
The self-employed continue to be brought out of the shadows
According to the regional authorities, in order to more effectively support small and medium-sized businesses, a number of changes should be made to the current legislation.
For example, the Arkhangelsk region proposed to replace the term "self-employment" with "entrepreneurial activity", since this "most corresponds to the content of the state service to promote self-employment of unemployed citizens."
In the Ivanovo region, it is considered necessary to make amendments providing for the expansion of the list of activities provided by self-employed citizens, including the types of activities for the decoration and repair of residential premises, dacha buildings, and physical training classes.
The Bryansk region considers it important to strengthen control over unscrupulous dairy producers with the help of the Mercury veterinary system.
And in the Kostroma and Magadan regions, they advocate for fixing the concept of "social entrepreneurship" in the regulatory and legal field and the directions of support for social entrepreneurship.
All proposals from the regions will be taken into account in the preparation of state programs to support small and medium-sized businesses, and the most important ones will be developed in the form of specific bills.
"All proposals from the regions will be taken into account in the preparation of state programs to support small and medium-sized businesses, and the most important ones will be developed in the form of specific bills," Andrei Kutepov assured.
