Pavel Ustinov joined the pickets in support of the defendants in the "Moscow case"
Actor Pavel Ustinov joined a series of single pickets "Freedom for All", which take place on Friday near the building of the presidential administration of the Russian Federation on The Old Square in Moscow, the correspondent of "Interfax" reports.
A series of pickets began on September 18 in support of Ustinov himself and has continued every day since then.
Currently, the participants of the action, replacing each other, stand holding a poster with the inscription "Freedom for all" and the names of those convicted and arrested after uncoordinated rallies in Moscow in the summer of 2019.
In addition to Ustinov, the poster bears the names of Yegor Zhukov, Kirill Zhukov, Danil Beglets, Evgeny Kovalenko, Konstantin Kotov, Ivan Podkopaev, Aidar Gubaidulin, Alexei Minyailo, Sergey Fomin, Samariddin Radjabov, Nikita Chirtsov, Eduard Malyshevsky, Vladislav Sinitsa.
On September 16, the Tver court of Moscow sentenced 24-year-old Ustinov to 3.5 years in a general regime colony on charges of using violence against a soldier of the OMON rosgvardia at an uncoordinated rally on August 3 in the center of Moscow (Part 2, Article 318 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation).
After that, on September 20, at the request of the Prosecutor General's Office, the court changed Ustinov's measure of restraint from detention to recognizance not to leave.
So, the petition for the release of Ustinov gained more than 112 thousand signatures per day.
Theater and film artists began a flash mob in support of their colleagues.
To participate in a single picket in solidarity with the actor on September 18, a queue lined up on the Old Square.
Human rights activists, journalists, scientists, teachers, doctors, Orthodox priests demanded a review of the case.
As Ustinov's sister Yulia told Interfax, her brother does not plan to speak at a rally on September 29 in the capital in support of the defendants in the "Moscow case".
Deliveries of "sanctions" to Russia fell 100 times
The Russian government estimated that the supply of agricultural products and food to Russia from countries subject to the Russian food embargo has decreased by more than 100 times since 2013.
According to a report sent to Russian President Vladimir Putin, in the first half of 2019, 31 thousand tons of products were imported from sanctioned countries against 3 million 442.2 thousand tons for the same period in 2013, Interfax reports.
At the same time, the cost of imported products decreased to $ 226.5 million from $ 4 billion 975.5 million, respectively.
We are talking about the supply of goods that are not subject to the embargo.
As indicated in the report, the dropped volumes of prohibited products were compensated by an increase in imports from the CIS countries, Africa, Southeast Asia, and Serbia.
Recall that at the end of August, the government extended until December 31, 2020, the validity of the rules for the destruction of agricultural products, raw materials and food, which are prohibited for import into Russia as part of counter-sanctions.
In a document posted on the official portal of legal information, it was noted that the validity of the rules was extended for another year - from December 31, 2019 to December 31, 2020.
Initially, the decree on the destruction of sanctions applied to products from the USA, THE EU, Australia, Norway and Canada.
Later, from August 13, 2015, Albania, Montenegro, Iceland, Liechtenstein "joined" this list, from January 1, 2016 - Ukraine.
A decree signed by Putin on the destruction of illegally imported into the country "sanctions" (products that fell under the food embargo, which Moscow imposed in response to anti-Russian sanctions of the West) came into force in 2015.
In turn, the government allowed the destruction of "sanctioned" food by any legal means.
As Western sanctions persisted, Russia also extended its retaliatory measures.
At the same time, this measure does not apply to products that citizens import for personal use.
The ban does not apply to the import of goods for personal consumption weighing up to 5 kilograms.
However, the head of the Presidential Council for the Development of Civil Society and Human Rights, Mikhail Fedotov, previously called the destruction of food products "simply immoral", and this, according to him, negatively affects the education of people.
Moreover, the initiative to prohibit the destruction of food products suitable for consumption was made by Rospotrebnadzor in early June.
After that, a similar recommendation to the government was given by the Human Rights Council under the President of the Russian Federation.
And Deputy Prime Minister Alexei Gordeev said that it is wrong to destroy food, and we need to think about how they can be used for their intended purpose, assessing the quality.
The head of the company was found guilty of tax evasion
By the verdict of the Leninsky District Court of Cheboksary, the director of LLC "Earth and Law" Vyacheslav Morozov was found guilty of committing crimes under paragraph "b" of Part 2 of Article 199 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (tax evasion from the organization by including knowingly false information in the tax return, committed on a particularly large scale) and Part 2 of Article 327 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (forgery of an official document,  granting rights and relieving from duties, for the purpose of using it, committed with the aim of concealing another crime and facilitating its commission).
This was reported by the press service of the investigative department of the ICR in Chuvashia.
From January 2008 to December 2009, Vyacheslav Morozov entered information about imperfect transactions into the tax accounting documents of the LLC.
According to fictitious documents, the company incurred additional costs, and, consequently, the amounts of taxes payable on value added and on the organization's profit of 11.2 million rubles were reduced.
Vyacheslav Morozov was sentenced to a suspended sentence of 3.5 years in prison.
By 2023, the first school of a new format will open in the center of the capital
A new school will be opened in Khamovniki.
According to the head of Moskomstroyinvest Anastasia Pyatova, they will create all conditions for self-realization and development of children's talents.
The educational institution was decided to be called "New Look".
This project will be supervised by the Moscow State Institute of International Relations of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Russia and the Foundation for the Economic Development of Higher Education.
The design of the building with an area of about 10 thousand "squares" is planned to begin next year.
They will finish the construction at the end of 2022, and in the next year they will begin to recruit the first students.
"The project provides for the creation of a publicly accessible, non-commercial educational space, which will be based on the traditions of the classical Moscow school and experimental methods," the press service of Moskomstroyinvest noted.
In Chile, began to build a telescope worth 1 billion euros
It is reported by TASS with reference to the press service of the European Southern Observatory (ESO).
According to ESO, this week the construction of the dome of the building where the E-ELT (European Extremely Large Telescope) telescope will be located, so far the most expensive and ambitious ground-based astronomical project, has officially begun.
Its total value, according to ESO estimates, will exceed one billion euros.
Most of this money will be spent on the manufacture of equipment and the construction of the observatory building.
The most expensive and complex component of the telescope is its record-breaking large mirror, whose diameter will be about 39 meters.
It will be assembled from 798 hexagonal segments measuring 1.4 meters.
This huge mirror, as well as two auxiliary reflective surfaces with a diameter of 4.2 and 3.75 meters, will help E-ELT to obtain the first detailed photographs of planets outside the solar system, stars in other galaxies, as well as to search for Earth's twins.
In addition, scientists will try to use this observatory to observe the vicinity of Sgr A *, a supermassive black hole at the center of the Milky Way.
Despite the fact that the construction of the dome has just begun, scientists, engineers and other specialists have been developing mirrors, scientific instruments and other components of the observatory for three years - since the announcement of the first plans for the construction of the E-ELT.
The contract for the production of the main mirror, whose total cost was about 400 million euros, was received by the German company SCHOTT and the French company Safran Reosc.
